The Juvenile and Family Court Journal is a quarterly peer-reviewed academic journal covering juvenile and family justice. It was established in 1949 as Juvenile Court Judges Journal, and was later renamed Juvenile Justice, and later renamed again to Journal of Juvenile & Family Courts. The journal obtained its current name in 1978. It is published by John Wiley & Sons and the National Council of Juvenile and Family Court Judges. The editors-in-chief are Mari Kay Bickett, Melissa Sickmund, and Maurice Portley. According to the Journal Citation Reports, the journal has a 2014 impact factor of 0.207.
